26/05/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The State Electoral Commission said Wednesday (25 May) that local elections in 13 municipalities and 6 counties would be repeated due to irregularities in the number of ballots cast and the number of registered voters. The revotes will be held between 29 May and 12 June. 
In other news Wednesday, leaders of the opposition Croatian People's Party (HNS) endorsed the party programme until the next general elections in 2007. After the session, HNS leader Vesna Pusic denied rumours that she will resign due to the party's poor performance in the local vote. (Vecernji list - 26/05/05; index.hr - 25/05/05)
